Altron, Bell Equipment and Metair Could Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-05-03T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/altron-bell-equipment-metair-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parenthesis and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell 510.40, or 1.6
percent, to 32,325.83 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg, the
lowest since April 19.  Allied Electronics Corp. Ltd. (ATN SJ): The investment
company with interests in communications equipment and power
cables reports earnings for the year ended Feb. 28. The shares
rose 46 cents, or 1.6 percent, to 29.26 rand.  Bell Equipment Ltd. (BEL)  : The handling machinery
manufacturer holds its annual general meeting at 11 a.m. The
stock retreated 5 cents, or 0.4 percent, to 13.35 rand.  Metair Investments Ltd. (MTA)  : The holding company for a
group that manufactures and supplies auto components holds its
annual general meeting at 2 p.m. The stock added 9 cents, or 0.6
percent, to 13.92 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in  Cape Town  at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  